messages.content:
thanks for this, great read! Definitely on the right track for where media is headed and self-participation in searching / researching information. Ever heard of the Dewey DDC system? lol. Something though to consider is the SEO market. Web pages are created solely for the purpose having higher priority algorithmic priority within a search engine. So to have only one source of creating knowledge graphs could be problematic even if you expand to social media platform and links, things that go viral are usually very generic content that anyone can relate to. This more so aligns with my ideals that all websites and social channels are hierarchical in nature and this could potentially enhance the website hierarchy if there aren't actual changes in nature to web traffic/knowledge sharing. 

Changes that I propose that may not be directly correlated with giantgra.ph , is that there can be a loss of English language and use of certain phrases and words. There is an opportunity here to counter-utilize this as ways to create web content that do not fit into these knowledge graphs, by creating strategies to win web traffic from an SEO standpoint since you are scraping only what is most seen and already documented as "validated" by the internet. Also, how would acronyms work here? Curious to see where acronyms are headed for the next decade as 3 letter acronyms could mean at least 10 different topics at least in due time without an alternative short way of identifying acronym. Happy to discuss on a call this framework if that's easier 😃
